<paragraph blockId="13.[125,815,1271,1328]" box="[125,709,1304,1328]" pageId="13" pageNumber="208">
<typeStatus box="[125,185,1304,1328]" pageId="13" pageNumber="208">Type</typeStatus>
species: 
<taxonomicName authority="Brown, 2005" authorityName="Brown" authorityYear="2005" box="[292,635,1304,1328]" class="Insecta" family="Tiphiidae" genus="Heligmothynnus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="208" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="microspinus" status="sp. n.">Heligmothynnus microspinus</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[644,709,1304,1328]" pageId="13" pageNumber="208" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="13.[125,1172,1369,1426]" pageId="13" pageNumber="208">
<emphasis box="[125,248,1369,1393]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="208">Etymology.</emphasis>
The generic name is derived from the Greek word heligma meaning curled and is a reference to the long coiled apical filament of the aedeagus.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="13.[125,1172,1467,1555]" pageId="13" pageNumber="208">
<emphasis box="[125,239,1467,1491]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="208">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Male: medial apical spine on the hypopygium small. Aedeagus with basal hoodlike structure with paired rounded apical lobes on the ventral margin laterally, and apical long and strongly coiled tape-like structure.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="13.[125,1173,1596,1685]" lastBlockId="14.[138,1185,971,1091]" lastPageId="14" lastPageNumber="209" pageId="13" pageNumber="208">
<emphasis box="[125,255,1596,1620]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="208">Description.</emphasis>
Male: similar to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Brown Basiparameres" authorityYear="1995" box="[461,591,1596,1620]" class="Insecta" family="Tiphiidae" genus="Tachyphron" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="208" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[461,591,1596,1620]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="208">Tachyphron</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but differs by having the apical hypopygial spine short and small (
<figureCitation box="[351,535,1629,1653]" captionStart="Figures 25–28" captionStartId="14.[138,207,1638,1657]" captionTargetBox="[182,1137,1318,1599]" captionTargetId="figure-100@14.[182,1140,1318,1602]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="Figures 25–28. Heligmothynnus spp., male hypopygia. (25) H. sabronensis. (26) H. microspinus. (27) H. atratus. (28) H. neoaratus. Scale bar: 0.25 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5214587" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5214587/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="208">Figures 25–28</figureCitation>
), and the genitalia (
<figureCitation box="[806,987,1629,1653]" captionStart="Figures 17–24" captionStartId="14.[138,207,885,904]" captionTargetBox="[183,1138,134,845]" captionTargetId="figure-128@14.[182,1140,133,849]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="Figures 17–24. Heligmothynnus spp., male genitalia, lateral and dorsal views. (17, 18) H. microspinus. (19, 20) H. atratus. (21, 22) H. neoaratus. (23, 24) H. sabronensis (note: basal ring not shown). Scale bar: 0.25 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5214585" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5214585/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="208">Figures 17–24</figureCitation>
) with (1) the basiparameres long and wide viewed both laterally and dorsally, and broadly emarginate apically; (2) the parameres narrow with the margins strongly curved and/or strongly convergent such that they almost appear sinusoidal in profile; and (3) the aedeagus differentiated into a basal hood-like structure with paired rounded apical lobes on the ventral margin laterally, and apically into a long and strongly coiled tape-like structure.
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5214585" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5214585" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5214585/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="209" startId="14.[138,207,885,904]" targetBox="[183,1138,134,845]" targetPageId="14">
<paragraph blockId="14.[138,1186,885,930]" pageId="14" pageNumber="209">
Figures 17–24. 
<taxonomicName box="[287,475,885,904]" class="Insecta" family="Tiphiidae" genus="Heligmothynnus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="209" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[287,427,885,904]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="209">Heligmothynnus</emphasis>
spp.
</taxonomicName>
, male genitalia, lateral and dorsal views. (17, 18) 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Brown" authorityYear="2005" box="[936,1066,885,904]" class="Insecta" family="Tiphiidae" genus="Heligmothynnus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="209" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="microspinus">
<emphasis box="[936,1066,885,904]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="209">H. microspinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. (19, 20) 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Cameron" authorityYear="1911" class="Insecta" family="Tiphiidae" genus="Aelurus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="209" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="atratus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="209">H. atratus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. (21, 22) 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Brown" authorityYear="2005" box="[295,409,911,930]" class="Insecta" family="Tiphiidae" genus="Heligmothynnus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="209" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="neoaratus">
<emphasis box="[295,409,911,930]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="209">H. neoaratus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. (23, 24) 
<taxonomicName box="[506,633,911,930]" class="Insecta" family="Tiphiidae" genus="Heligmothynnus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="209" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sabronensis">
<emphasis box="[506,633,911,930]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="209">H. sabronensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(note: basal ring not shown). Scale bar: 0.25 mm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="14.[138,1185,1132,1220]" pageId="14" pageNumber="209">
<emphasis box="[138,242,1132,1156]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="209">Remarks.</emphasis>
Four species, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Cameron" authorityYear="1911" box="[422,537,1132,1155]" class="Insecta" family="Tiphiidae" genus="Aelurus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="209" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="atratus">
<emphasis box="[422,537,1132,1155]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="209">H. atratus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Brown" authorityYear="2005" box="[556,722,1132,1156]" class="Insecta" family="Tiphiidae" genus="Heligmothynnus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="209" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="microspinus">
<emphasis box="[556,722,1132,1156]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="209">H. microspinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Brown" authorityYear="2005" box="[741,886,1132,1155]" class="Insecta" family="Tiphiidae" genus="Heligmothynnus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="209" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="neoaratus">
<emphasis box="[741,886,1132,1155]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="209">H. neoaratus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[950,1111,1132,1156]" class="Insecta" family="Tiphiidae" genus="Heligmothynnus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="209" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sabronensis">
<emphasis box="[950,1111,1132,1156]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="209">H. sabronensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, from New 
<collectingCountry box="[203,288,1164,1188]" name="Guinea-Bissau" pageId="14" pageNumber="209">Guinea</collectingCountry>
or the adjacent island of Biak are known. All are represented only from a single locality and a single male specimen (
<figureCitation box="[643,764,1196,1220]" captionStart="Figure 59" captionStartId="27.[125,185,910,929]" captionTargetBox="[170,1125,138,870]" captionTargetId="figure-194@27.[170,1128,133,874]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="Figure 59. Distribution of Deuterothynnus spp. and Heligmothynnus spp. (note the coincident collecting of D. fulvicentratus with H. microspinus, and D. fulvisetatus with D. parallelus)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5214599" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5214599/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="209">Figure 59</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
